Class CharacterArrayConverter

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class CharacterArrayConverter
extends SizeConverter<char[]>

This class provides a converter that is able to read and write arrays of char values. First the converter reads or writes the length of the char array. Thereafter the char values are read or written.

Example usage (1). 

   // create an char array
   
   char[] array = {'C', 'h', 'a', 'r', '-', 'A', 'r', 'r', 'a', 'y'};
   
   // create a byte array output stream
   
   ByteArrayOutputStream output = new ByteArrayOutputStream();
   
   // write array to the output stream
   
   CharacterArrayConverter.DEFAULT_INSTANCE.write(new DataOutputStream(output), array);
   
   // create a byte array input stream on the output stream
   
   ByteArrayInputStream input = new ByteArrayInputStream(output.toByteArray());
   
   // reset the array
   
   array = null;
   
   // read array from the input stream
   
   array = CharacterArrayConverter.DEFAULT_INSTANCE.read(new DataInputStream(input));
   
   // print the array
   
   for (char c : array)
       System.out.println(c);
       
   // close the streams after use
   
   input.close();
   output.close();

See Also:
DataInput, DataOutput, IOException, Serialized Form

Field Detail

DEFAULT_INSTANCE

public static final CharacterArrayConverter DEFAULT_INSTANCE
This instance can be used for getting a default instance of character array converter. It is similar to the Singleton Design Pattern (for further details see Creational Patterns, Prototype in Design Patterns: Elements of Reusable Object-Oriented Software by Erich Gamma, Richard Helm, Ralph Johnson, and John Vlissides) except that there are no mechanisms to avoid the creation of other instances of a character array converter.

read

public char[] read(java.io.DataInput dataInput,
                   char[] object)
            throws java.io.IOException
Reads an array of char values from the specified data input and returns the restored char array.

When the specified char array is null this implementation returns a new array of char values, otherwise the size of the specified char array has to be sufficient.
